section.section:
"Recipient of services" includes:
An individual in a public facility under the Maryland Mental Hygiene Law;
An individual in a facility for an evaluation required under the Maryland Developmental Disabilities Law;
An individual in a residential, public facility or a facility from which this State obtains residential care under the Maryland Developmental Disabilities Law;
An individual to whom juvenile screening or treatment services are provided under § 9-227(b)(1)(ii) of the Human Services Article; and
An individual in a private therapeutic group home from which this State obtains residential care under the Maryland Mental Hygiene Law.
